'''耶澤羅撞擊坑'''（{{lang-en|Jezero}}）<ref group="註">斯拉夫語系中的「[[Ј|Ј]]」的發音為 {{IPA4|j}}，和英語的「[[Y|Y]]」相同。</ref>，又譯'''耶澤洛撞擊坑'''或'''傑澤羅撞擊坑'''，是[[火星|火星]]北半球的一座[[撞擊坑|撞擊坑]]，直徑47.52公里，座落於[[伊希地平原|伊希地平原]]與[[大瑟提斯高原|大瑟提斯高原]]的交界帶北緣，中心座標18.41°N，77.69°E<ref name = usgs>{{cite web | url = https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/14300 | title = Jezero | work = Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature | agency = [[IAU|IAU]] / [[USGS|USGS]] / [[NASA|NASA]] | accessdate = 2020-07-30 | archive-date = 2021-03-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210321020534/https://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/14300 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。該撞擊坑最晚約於36億年前的{{le|諾亞紀|Noachian}}晚期（或{{le|赫斯珀利亞紀|Hesperian}}早期）形成<ref name = Hiesinger2004>{{ cite journal | author = Hiesinger, H.; Head, J. W. | title = The Syrtis Major volcanic province, Mars: Synthesis from Mars Global Surveyor data | journal = ''Journal of Geophysical Research Atmospheres'' | volume = 109 | pages = E01004 | year = 2004 | issn = 0148-0227 | doi = 10.1029/2003JE002143 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/251429443_The_Syrtis_Major_volcanic_province_Mars_Synthesis_from_Mars_Global_Surveyor_data }}</ref>，內部富含[[黏土礦物|黏土礦物]]，在形成初期極可能是一座長期存在的[[湖泊|湖泊]]。撞擊坑的名稱「耶澤羅」源自[[波士尼亞與赫塞哥維納|波士尼亞與赫塞哥維納]]中部的[[湖村|湖村]]（{{lang-sr|Језеро}} / {{transl|sr|''Jezero''}}），這個名稱在許多[[斯拉夫語族|斯拉夫語族]]語言中都是指「湖泊」，即是由此而來<ref name = Witze>{{cite web | url = https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-02257-w | author = Witze, Alexandra | title = NASA has launched the most ambitious Mars rover ever built: here’s what happens next | publisher = [[自然_(期刊)|Nature]] | date = 2020-07-30 | access-date = 2020-07-30 | archive-date = 2021-03-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210307201728/https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-02257-w | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

撞擊坑的邊緣有兩座扇狀沉積區域，與類似河道的構造相通，普遍認為是當時來自[[尼利槽溝|尼利槽溝]]的河水沿河道沖破坑緣，匯入坑內形成湖泊之處<ref name = Fassett2005>{{ cite journal | author = Fassett, C. I.; Head, J. W. | title = Fluvial Sedimentary Deposits on Mars: Ancient Deltas in a Crater Lake in the Nili Fossae Region | journal = ''Geophysical Research Letters'' | volume = 321 | issue = 14 | pages = 1–4 | year = 2005 | issn = 0094-8276 | doi = 10.1029/2005GL023456 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/251220074_Fluvial_sedimentary_deposits_on_Mars_Ancient_deltas_in_a_crater_lake_in_the_Nili_Fossae_region }}</ref><ref name = Ehlmann2008>{{cite journal | author = Ehlmann, B. L.; Mustard, J. F.; Fassett, C. I.; Schon, S. C.; Head, J. W.; Marais, D. J. D.; Grant, John A.; Murchie, Scott L. | title = Clay minerals in delta deposits and organic preservation potential on Mars | journal = ''Nature Geoscience'' | volume = 1 | issue = 6 | pages = 355–358 | year = 2008 | issn = 1752-0894 | doi = 10.1038/ngeo207 | url = https://repository.si.edu/handle/10088/16530 | access-date = 2020-07-30 | archive-date = 2021-03-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210307201733/https://repository.si.edu/handle/10088/16530 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。此外，探測衛星拍攝的影像顯示該區域尚留有{{le|河曲沙洲|Point bar}}與[[倒轉地形|倒轉河道]]，對這些地質構造的研究顯示，當耶澤羅撞擊坑還是湖泊時，注入湖泊的[[地表逕流|地表逕流]]或可源源不絕的供給水源，因此湖水水位長期都沒有明顯變動<ref name = Goudge2017>{{cite conference | author = Goudge, T. A.; Mohrig, D.; Cardenas, B. T.; Hughes, C. M.; Fassett, C. I. | title = Stratigraphy and Evolution of Delta Channel Deposits, Jezero Crater Mars | conference = The 48<sup>th</sup> Lunar and Planetary Science Conference | year = 2017 | url = https://www.hou.usra.edu/meetings/lpsc2017/pdf/1195.pdf | access-date = 2020-07-30 | archive-date = 2021-02-20 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210220023619/https://www.hou.usra.edu/meetings/lpsc2017/pdf/1195.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

由於地質古老，地形豐富，加上可能保存早期生命訊息的三角洲，[[美國航太總署|美國航太總署]]於2018年擇定耶澤羅撞擊坑為[[火星2020探測車任務|火星2020探測車任務]]的著陸地點<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-announces-landing-site-for-mars-2020-rover | author = Hautaluoma, Grey | title = NASA Announces Landing Site for Mars 2020 Rover | publisher = [[NASA|NASA]] | accessdate = 2018-11-20 | archive-date = 2020-07-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200721063828/https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-announces-landing-site-for-mars-2020-rover/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

== 古湖泊系統 ==
[[File:NASA-Mars-JezeroCrater-20181116.jpg|thumb]]
2000年代中期，[[行星地質學|行星地質學家]]透過[[火星全球探勘者號|火星全球探勘者號]]、[[2001火星奧德賽號|2001火星奧德賽號]]和[[火星快車號|火星快車號]]等探測衛星記錄到的資料，在當時未獲命名的耶澤羅撞擊坑周圍發現數個峽谷系統，並在這些地點都檢測出含有屬於[[黏土礦物|黏土礦物]]的[[膨潤石族|膨潤石族]]礦物（smectite）。由於黏土礦物需在有水的環境下形成，能以此推論此處一度有水存在。此外，撞擊坑西側和北側的峽谷內部都有發達的彎曲溝槽，被認為是在撞擊坑形成後不久，由[[曲流|曲流]]形塑而成。而兩座峽谷在與撞擊坑相通處也都有[[三角洲|三角洲]]沉積地形，顯示水流曾沿此二峽谷注入撞擊坑，形成一座深逾200公尺的湖泊；其中西側的三角洲有明顯的交錯分層沉積，呈現典型的鳥趾狀外觀（birdfoot delta）。撞擊坑東緣則連接另一座峽谷，推測是湖水流出的河道，通往地勢更低的[[伊希地平原|伊希地平原]]<ref name = Fassett2005/>。

美國行星地質學家[[山繆·尚恩|山繆·尚恩]]（Samuel C. Schon）等人由撞擊坑的地貌和沉積模型推算，西側的三角洲需耗時100萬至1000萬年才能形成<ref name = Schon2012>{{ cite journal | author = Schon, S. C.; Head, J. W.; Fassett, C. I. | title = An overfilled lacustrine system and progradational delta in Jezero crater, Mars: Implications for Noachian climate | journal = ''Planetary and Space Science'' | volume = 67 | issue = 1 | pages = 28–45 | year = 2012 | issn = 0032-0633 | doi = 10.1016/j.pss.2012.02.003 | url = https://www.researchgate.net/publication/258688201_An_overfilled_lacustrine_system_and_progradational_delta_in_Jezero_crater_Mars_Implications_for_Noachian_climate }}</ref>。

